# Frontend Telegram UX Rules

- Use Telegram Mini App APIs correctly: `ready()`, `expand()`, theme params, native Back/Main buttons.
- Preserve SPA navigation behavior; no full page reloads for internal transitions.
- Design mobile-first for Telegram viewport and safe-area constraints.
- Keep MURU visual identity fixed: Montserrat, approved palette, no unauthorized style drift.
- Reuse shared UI components before adding new page-local variants.

## Product UX Constraints

- Variants (color/size) must be inside one product card, not separate products.
- Zero-stock products stay visible with "Под заказ" and notify flow.
- Bottom navigation keeps 5 core tabs: Catalog, Search, Cart, Favorites, Profile.
- Any new component that changes interaction pattern should be documented before merge.
